This paper deals with secure network coding, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the security aspect, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the transmission of messages, which can be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the statistical dependence of messages, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the implementation of network coding, which can be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
